            <title>[JCR-980] Single quote in contains function is not parsed correctly</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-980</link>
                <project id="10591" key="JCR">Jackrabbit Content Repository</project>
                        <description>If there is a single quote in the contains statement the parser will throw an exception.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Example:&lt;br/&gt;
//element(*, nt:resource)[jcr:contains(., &amp;#39;it&amp;#39;&amp;#39;s fun&amp;#39;)]&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
The LuceneQueryBuilder replaces the single quote with a double quote and hence the lucene fulltext query parser fails because there is a missing closing double quote. Not sure why this is done in the code, maybe this is a left over from an early JSR 170 draft.</description>
